Job Title: Data Science Manager – Fraud Risk Engine
Ad Text:
We are seeking a highly skilled and experienced Fraud Risk Engine Decision Scientist to lead the design, implementation, and optimisation of real-time fraud detection use cases using a fraud risk engine. This role bridges business understanding with technical expertise, enabling proactive fraud prevention through data-driven decisioning.
 

You will collaborate closely with business stakeholders to define fraud scenarios, identify and source relevant data, configure detection logic (rules, thresholds, models), and ensure accurate and timely decisions and alerts.
 

The ideal candidate will have extensive experience in fraud risk engine product implementation, fraud detection techniques, and a strong understanding of financial crime prevention strategies, including the use of cloud-based data services like AWS.

Key Responsibilities:

Partner with business teams to define and refine fraud detection use cases based on emerging threats, customer behaviour, and regulatory needs.

Identify, source, clean, and organise relevant data to support fraud detection. Perform exploratory data analysis to uncover patterns and insights.

Configure and tune rules, thresholds, and predictive models within the fraud risk engine to enable real-time decisioning.

Translate business needs into statistical or machine learning models. Validate and monitor model performance, ensuring alignment with governance standards.

Ensure fraud decisions are accurate, timely, and actionable. Design alerting mechanisms that balance fraud prevention with customer experience.

Present analytical findings and model outcomes to technical and non-technical stakeholders. Provide recommendations for continuous improvement.

Collaborate with cross-functional teams including architects, engineering, compliance, and business units to implement new fraud prevention initiatives.

Provide expertise during audits and compliance reviews related to fraud prevention controls.

About the role

We're seeking an Enforcement Data Engineer to join our Customer & Technology business unit, partnering with Customer Solutions & Australian Markets. You'll play a strategic role in optimising core infringement processes, driving continuous improvement within Operations to improve efficiency and cost. You'll identify enforcement reform opportunities using automated data extraction, ingestion, and loading to streamline processes and deliver impactful change.


Day-to-day, you will

Lead the creation and deployment of internal RPA/AI agents to automate infringement-related processes across the full enforcement lifecycle.
Work with internal systems (Salesforce, Yellowfin, Securedocs) to extract, transform, and load (ETL) data into user interfaces
Build data and ETL pipelines and support the ingestion and processing of structured and unstructured data across batch processes.
Support the Operations leadership team in analysing and remediating identified data issues and collaborate with key stakeholders to address challenges swiftly and effectively.
Monitor performance metrics-including volumes and camera automation rates-using AI-powered analytics to generate actionable insights.
Develop and recommend improvements to infringement business processes based on sound research and analysis, ensuring process improvements align with regulatory requirements and risks are managed appropriately.


This role will suit someone with a curious mind and transferrable skills and experiences, including:

5 years in data engineering, business transformation or operational excellence
Proven ability to implement tech and automation solutions that drive efficiency
Tertiary qualification in a technical / analytical field e.g. computer sciences, maths or physics
Excellent communication, facilitation and change leadership skills
Proficiency with process mapping tools (e.g. Visio)


With a career at Transurban, you'll enjoy a range of benefits, including:

A range of flexible working and leave options, including the option to purchase an additional six weeks of leave each year
16 weeks paid parental leave (regardless of gender or carer status), with no waiting period, with Superannuation paid during unpaid leave as well

About your role

As a Senior Strategy Analyst, you'll be a key force behind shaping our strategic direction and driving high-impact decisions. This role is ideal for someone who thrives at the intersection of commercial thinking and analytical depth—transforming complex data into clear, actionable insights that fuel growth and sharpen our competitive edge.

Reporting to Head of Strategy (who reports to CFO), you'll work closely with cross-functional teams including Finance, HR, Operations, and Commercial, identifying opportunities, assessing risks, and supporting executive-level initiatives that influence the future of the business.

Key Responsibilities

Lead end-to-end strategic projects—from hypothesis development to execution
Analyse market trends, competitor movements, and internal performance metrics
Support the annual Corporate Planning process with data-driven insights
Develop and present strategic recommendations to senior stakeholders
Contribute to corporate development activities including M&A, partnerships, and investments
Build financial models and scenario analyses to forecast outcomes and guide decisions
Collaborate across departments to shape and refine business strategies
Track execution of strategic initiatives and measure success against key KPIs

Who are we looking for?

Bachelor's degree in Business, Finance, Economics or a related field (MBA highly regarded)
5+ years' experience in strategy consulting, corporate strategy, or a similar analytical role
Exceptional problem-solving and critical thinking skills
Advanced proficiency in Excel, PowerPoint, and strategic modelling tools
Strong communication and stakeholder engagement skills
Proven ability to manage multiple priorities and deliver results in a fast-paced environment

Benefits at IXOM

For a start, you'll work for a large global organisation, where you'll not only earn a competitive salary, but you'll also have access to an Employee Assistance Program, a recognition program, and a range of health and wellness benefits and discounts.

Our wellbeing program is second to none, and we offer a range of education assistance and learning resources, as well as secondment and promotion opportunities to help you grow both personally and professionally.

We support what's important to you by promoting workplace giving, diversity and providing volunteering leave, and, of course, we offer flexible working wherever possible.
